President Biden delivered a speech at the Washington Hilton in Washington, D.C., addressing the importance of a free press and advocating for the release of American journalists being held hostage or wrongfully detained abroad. He mentioned Evan and Austin, two journalists who are currently detained in Russia and Syria respectively, and pledged to work towards securing their release. The President also acknowledged other Americans being held unjustly in countries such as Iran, Venezuela, and China. He emphasized that journalism is not a crime and praised the role of the free press in a democratic society. President Biden also made jokes throughout his speech, touching on topics such as his age, the media, and political opponents. He concluded by urging everyone to embrace truth and restore the soul of the nation.